 f(K_{n,d}) = \\mathbf c_d \\cdot \\Omega(K), $$ where $\\Omega(K)$ is the\naffine surface area of $K$, and $\\mathbf c_d$ is an unknown vector not\ndepending on $K$. We compute $\\mathbf c_d$ explicitly in dimensions up to\n$d=10$ and also solve the analogous problem for random polytopes with vertices\ndistributed uniformly on the sphere.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Jul 2019 14:09:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 6 Oct 2019 10:14:30 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 12 Jul 2020 19:33:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-14"}
